-- Antonio Esfandiari Wins $18.3 Million in Poker’s Biggest Payout
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-07-04T03:10:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/antonio-esfandiari-wins-18-3-million-in-poker-s-biggest-payout.html
Antonio Esfandiari won $18.3 million,
poker’s biggest payout, in the $1 million buy-in charity
tournament at the  World Series  of Poker.  Esfandiari, a 33-year-old poker professional from the U.S.,
beat British player Sam Trickett, 25, on the final hand in the
tournament at the Rio All-Suite Hotel & Casino in Las Vegas.  Trickett collects $10.1 million. Greenlight Capital Inc.
co-founder  David Einhorn  was third, winning $4.35 million.
Einhorn, 43, said he’ll donate his winnings to the charity City
Year.  “I just knew I was going to win,” Esfandiari told ESPN in
a televised interview. “I just had to put it out there and
believe it, and sometimes it comes true.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
